is that this advocacy—vital advocacy—expands our view of what counts as life and shows us what it would mean for the moral standing of human life to be extended to life itself.Including short interviews with celebrated ecological writer Dorion Sagan, former NASA Planetary Protection Officer Catharine Conley, and leading figure in Indigenous and environmental studies Kyle Whyte, Every Living Thing provides a capacious view of life in the natural world. This book is a must-read for anyone interested in biodiversity, bioethics, and the environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aEarth First activism.  aKenneth Burke.  aLife.  aMartian microbes.  aStanding Rock Sioux tribe.  aVoluntary Human Extinction Movement.  abiocentrism.  abiopolitics.  aecocriticsm.  aecofascism.  aenvironmental activism.  aenvironmental advocacy.  aenvironmental ethics.  arhetoric.  avitalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079775640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271096285?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271096285423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271096285/original  a978-3-11-079775-6  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131922-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929